Package mavlc.error_reporting

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    ArgumentCountError
    Error class to signal a mismatch in the argument count between function definition and call expression.
    CompilationError
    Abstract super-type of all errors thrown by the mavlc compiler.
    ConstantAssignmentError
    Error class to signal a non-permitted assignment to a constant value.
    DuplicateCaseException
    Error class to signal duplicate (default) cases in a SwitchStmt.
    InapplicableOperationError
    Error class to signal that an operation is not applicable to the type of the underlying element.
    MisplacedReturnError
    Error class to signal a misplaced return statement.
    MissingMainFunctionError  
    MissingReturnError
    Error class to signal a missing return statement for a non-void function.
    NonConstantExpressionError
    Error class to signal that an expression that must be constant wasn't actually a constant expression.
    OverwritingDeclarationError
    Error class to signal a non-permitted overwriting of an already existing declaration.
    RecordElementError
    Error class to signal an error with an element of a record.
    StructureDimensionError
    Error class to signal a mismatch in the dimensions of a matrix or vector.
    SyntaxError
    Error class to signal a syntax error during parsing.
    TypeError
    Error class to signal a type mismatch.
    UndeclaredReferenceError
    Error class to signal a reference to a non-declared entity.
